snippet: In Florida, where the Jets beat Jacksonville, Tim Tebow had nothing to do for the winning team. He might have been luckier to have ended up with the losers.
abstract: Harvey Araton On Pro Football column observes that New York Jets backup quarterback Tim Tebow did not appear in one measly play in Jets victory over Jacksonville Jaguars, suggesting that the Tebow phenomenon may have officially expired in an atmosphere of sustained indifference.
lead_paragraph: In Florida, where the Jets beat Jacksonville, Tim Tebow had nothing to do for the winning team. He might have been luckier to have ended up with the losers.

headline.seo: Tim Tebow, in Jacksonville With Jets, Doesn’t Play
headline.main: Tebow Returns Home but Seems to Belong Nowhere
